metadata.name: Arcane
metadata.description:
Since my childhood, I've been trying to find a key to understanding the world. I tried to approach it with contemplation, reading, and drawings. However, my efforts were unsuccessful. It made me discouraged. But it seems, I found a method of cognition of our world.
This painting isn't digitally created. This is made without hands. It's a collaboration with Mother Nature. I trigger chemical-physical processes on cotton paper and all happen according to the laws of nature. I don't know what be there until the last moment and just convey that in digital view.
Itâ€™s a conversation with nature and this process is intangible. I've caught the moment when nature creates itself. I feel an arcane mystery of nature here and I must solve this in order to understand the world.

#1

Cotton paper, chemical-physical processes.
